        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20UnivLE.2E.7Bu.2C.20v.7D.20implies.20UnivLE.2E.7Bmax.20u.20v.2C.20v.7D.3F/near/483371411\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"197836\">Jireh Loreaux</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20UnivLE.2E.7Bu.2C.20v.7D.20implies.20UnivLE.2E.7Bmax.20u.20v.2C.20v.7D.3F/near/483316106\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>yeah, there's nothing that says universes are linearly ordered.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I did prove <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=univLE_total#doc\">docs#univLE_total</a> but I failed to prove the statement in the title. I think as Ruben said, the constraints on universe <code>max</code> is not strong enough to prove it. I just tried to search for an axiomatic characterization of the max function in a linear order, but I didn't find any; instead I found <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/questions/472114/what-is-known-about-the-theory-of-natural-numbers-with-only-0-successor-and-max\">this MO question</a> and it seems the only difference is that it assumes injectivity of the successor function. Since we have <code>UnivLE.{u, v} ↔ Nonempty (Ordinal.{u} ↪ Ordinal.{v})</code>, this injectivity should be equivalent to <code>(Ordinal.{u+1} ≃ Ordinal.{v+1}) → (Ordinal.{u} ≃ Ordinal.{v})</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think the axiomation of universe levels in Lean (including <code>max</code>) can be found in page 7 of <a href=\"https://github.com/digama0/lean-type-theory/releases\"><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110049\">@Mario Carneiro</span>'s paper</a>. But then I'm confused, as the third axiom in the 5th line seems to be exactly what we want:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>≤</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>≤</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>max</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≤</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">l_1 \\le l +n, l_2 \\le l+ n \\Rightarrow \\max(l_1,l_2) \\le l +n.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0197em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7778em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0197em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7778em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⇒</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">max</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0197em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0197em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≤</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7778em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>(so is the package prooftree not usable here?)</p>",
