    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20UnivLE.2E.7Bu.2C.20v.7D.20implies.20UnivLE.2E.7Bmax.20u.20v.2C.20v.7D.3F/near/483371411\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"197836\">Jireh Loreaux</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20UnivLE.2E.7Bu.2C.20v.7D.20implies.20UnivLE.2E.7Bmax.20u.20v.2C.20v.7D.3F/near/483316106\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>yeah, there's nothing that says universes are linearly ordered.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I did prove <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=univLE_total#doc\">docs#univLE_total</a> but I failed to prove the statement in the title. I think as Ruben said, the constraints on universe <code>max</code> is not strong enough to prove it. I just tried to search for an axiomatic characterization of the max function in a linear order, but I didn't find any; instead I found <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/questions/472114/what-is-known-about-the-theory-of-natural-numbers-with-only-0-successor-and-max\">this MO question</a> and it seems the only difference is that it assumes injectivity of the successor function. Since we have <code>UnivLE.{u, v} ↔ Nonempty (Ordinal.{u} ↪ Ordinal.{v})</code>, this injectivity should be equivalent to <code>(Ordinal.{u+1} ≃ Ordinal.{v+1}) → (Ordinal.{u} ≃ Ordinal.{v})</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I have thought about this a bit and I think the explanation is that <code>univLE_total</code> doesn't actually prove that universes are totally ordered. <code>UnivLE</code> is not the ordering relation on universes, it is more like an extension of it (to a linear order), while <code>max</code> is the join in the real ordering relation on universes</p>",
        "id": 483441998,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1732095550
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The real ordering relation on universes is defined by whether <code>max u v = v</code> is defeq</p>",
