        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1732095667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110049\">Mario Carneiro</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20UnivLE.2E.7Bu.2C.20v.7D.20implies.20UnivLE.2E.7Bmax.20u.20v.2C.20v.7D.3F/near/483442369\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The real ordering relation on universes is defined by whether <code>max u v = v</code> is defeq</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Ah, that makes sense. So I guess the property of real ordering of universes is not even something we can argue inside Lean, right?</p>",
